  "texts": [
    "When the agent reaches the endpoint or collides with other vehicles, it is considered as the end of the scenario.",
    "The reflection module will then update the shared-memory module.",
    "When the update is completed, the agent completes a round of training in that scene.",
    "After every 20 rounds of training, 20 randomly generated scenarios are selected and fixed for testing the trained agents in KoMA.",
    "Parameter Value The lane count of the highway main road 2 The lane count of the on-ramp merging road 1 The length of on-ramp merging road 120 m The initialization speed of vehicles range from 20 to 25 m/s The spacing of the spawn points 40 m The initial location noise range from -10 to 10 m The count of LLM controlled vehicles 2 The count of intelligent driver model vehicles 5 Policy frequency 2 HzBaseline MARL-based model: The baseline MARL method is \"deep multi-agent reinforcement learning for highway on-ramp merging in mixed traffic\" [41], which develop an efficient and scalable MARL framework that can be used in dynamic traffic where the communication topology could be time-varying."
